
* Antieau 9Weeks

"Everything comes down to the cotangent complex" (e.g. def/moduli th,
HH, dRcohom, prismcoh). Kahler diffs are the classical construction of
the cotan cx.



Given $k\to R$ of rings, $M$ an $R-\text{module}$, a $k-\textbf{derivation}$
(of $R$ in $M$) is function $d:R\to M$ with properties
$d(r+s)=d(r)+d(s)$, 
Leibniz rule (no grading), and $k\in \ker d$.

*Kahler differential* $\Omega^1_{R/k}$ is free $R$-module generated by
$dr$ for every $r\in R$ quotient the relations. Only a module (not
ring -- consider $d(r+s)D(r+s)$).

